From bb8879f8cb99d290506e6822ff3f847a3dc828c4 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: utzcoz <utzcoz@outlook.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 00:19:06 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] vr: add BGRA swapchain-format switch and fix Linux
 SharedImage backing

Adds --webxr-openxr-swapchain-format=rgba|bgra (device::switches),
forwarded from the browser into the isolated XR utility process via
ServiceProcessHost WithExtraCommandLineSwitches (switches are not copied
to utility processes by default). OpenXrGraphicsBindingVulkan::
GetSwapchainFormat() honors it with an ordered preference list (SRGB
preferred over UNORM, the non-selected ordering kept as a fallback), and
CreateSharedImages maps the viz SharedImage format to match (kBGRA_8888
for both BGRA SRGB and UNORM) so colors are not swizzled. The mock OpenXR
runtime now advertises both orderings so the selection is unit-tested.
Default behavior (rgba) is unchanged.

Also drops SHARED_IMAGE_USAGE_SCANOUT from the swapchain SharedImages.
The images are blitted into the OpenXR swapchain, never scanned out, and
requesting SCANOUT on a LINEAR (modifier 0) NativePixmap left no backing
factory able to satisfy it -- CreateSharedImage returned null and the
session crashed (scoped_refptr DCHECK), so no frames ever displayed. This
affected RGBA and BGRA identically.
